  "prompt": "What are the alternatives to WalkMe?",
  "response": "If you're considering alternatives to WalkMe, a digital adoption platform, there are several options available that cater to various needs and budgets. Some popular alternatives include:\n\n1. **Whatfix**: Offers in-app guidance and performance support with easy-to-create walkthroughs and guided tours.\n\n2. **Pendo**: Provides product analytics, in-app messaging, and user guidance tools suitable for both web and mobile applications.\n\n3. **Appcues**: Known for its user onboarding and feature adoption capabilities, allowing for the creation of customizable flows without needing developer input.\n\n4. **Userlane**: Focuses on providing interactive guidance and automated onboarding for software applications to improve user experience.\n\n5. **Inline Manual**: Delivers interactive tutorials and in-app messaging to guide users through product features effectively.\n\n6. **HelpHero**: Designed for creating product tours and enhancing user onboarding processes with minimal setup.\n\n7. **Tour My App**: Offers a straightforward approach to in-app tours and user guidance, suitable for smaller teams or less complex needs.\n\n8. **Guidde**: A platform that helps create video walkthroughs and step-by-step guides alongside text-based options.\n\n9. **Chameleon**: Specializes in in-product user engagement with features like product tours, tooltips, and surveys to gather user feedback.\n\n10. **Usetiful**: Provides multi-language product tours, checklists, and in-app messages designed for user engagement and onboarding.\n\nThese platforms generally offer a range of features from simple guides to advanced analytics and user segmentation, so the best choice will depend on your specific requirements, such as ease of use, budget, target audience, and feature set.",
